As a sophomore he was a preseason top 50 watchlist selection for the [[John R. Wooden Award]] and the [[Naismith College Player of the Year]].<ref name=BTMBWR20111109>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/110911aaa.html|title=Big Ten Men's Basketball Weekly Release - Nov. 9, 2011: All 12 Big Ten teams open 2011-12 season this weekend |date=2011-11-14|accessdate=2011-11-14|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref> In the 3-game November 21&ndash;23 [[2011 Maui Invitational Tournament]], Hardaway scored 60 points against the #8 [[2011<U+2013>12 Memphis Tigers men's basketball team|Memphis Tigers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=313250235|title=Tim Hardaway Jr. leads No.15 Michigan to win|accessdate=2011-11-24|date=2011-11-21|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> #6 [[2011<U+2013>12 Duke Blue Devils men's basketball team|Duke Blue Devils]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=313260150|title=Austin Rivers' 20 points lead sharp-shooting Duke past Michigan|accessdate=2011-11-24|date=2011-11-22|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> and [[2011<U+2013>12 Pacific-12 Conference men's basketball season|2011<U+2013>12 Pacific-12 season]] favorite [[2011<U+2013>12 UCLA Bruins men's basketball team|UCLA Bruins]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/la-sp-1029-ucla-basketball-pac12-20111029,0,5239295.story|title=UCLA picked to win Pac-12 basketball title, but the vote is close|accessdate=2011-11-24|date=2011-10-28|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Bolch, Ben}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=313270026|title=Michigan tops UCLA, finishes third at Maui Invitational|accessdate=2011-11-24|date=2011-11-23|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> which helped the team finish in third place and earned him a place on the All-Tournament team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.detnews.com/article/20111123/SPORTS0201/111230434/1361/Michigan-senior-Zack-Novak-finds-scoring-touch-in-Maui|title=Michigan senior Zack Novak finds scoring touch in Maui|accessdate=2011-11-24|date=2011-11-23|work=[[The Detroit News]]|author=Beard, Ron}} {{Dead link|date=April 2012|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> For his performance at the Maui Classic, he earned the Big Ten Player of the Week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/112811aaa.html|title=Michigan Sweeps Weekly Honors: Burke and Hardaway Jr. Lead Wolverines to Third-Place Finish at Maui Invitational |accessdate=2011-11-28|date=2011-11-28|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=BigTen.org}}</ref> In addition, he was named Big Ten Player of the Week by College Sports Madness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/112811aab.html|title=Hardaway, Burke Sweep Big Ten Conference Weekly Honors|accessdate=2011-11-28|date=2011-11-28|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com}}</ref> In the subsequent game, he picked up two fouls against [[2011<U+2013>12 Virginia Cavaliers men's basketball team|Virginia]] in the first 5:33 and sat the final 14:27 of the first half.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/112911aac.html|title=Postgame Notes: Virginia 70, #14 Michigan 58|accessdate=2011-12-02|date=2011-11-29|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com}}</ref> He finished the November 29 contest with just 5 points, snapping a 22-game double-digit scoring streak.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=313330258|title=(15) Michigan 58 (5-2, 0-1 away); Virginia 70 (6-1, 4-0 home)|accessdate=2011-12-02|date=2011-11-29|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> On December 29, he opened the [[2011<U+2013>12 Big Ten Conference men's basketball season]] with 26 points against [[2011-12 Penn State Nittany Lions men's basketball team|Penn State]], despite making only 1 of 7 three-point shots.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=313630130|title=Penn St 53 (8-6, 0-1 Big Ten); (16) Michigan 71 (11-2, 1-0 Big Ten)|accessdate=2012-01-08|date=2011-12-29|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> On January 8, 2012, he had his second career double-double with 17 points and 10 rebounds against 19th ranked [[2011<U+2013>12 Wisconsin Badgers men's basketball team|Wisconsin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=320080130|title=(19) Wisconsin 41 (12-5, 1-3 Big Ten); (13) Michigan 59 (13-3, 3-1 Big Ten)|accessdate=2012-01-08|date=2012-01-08|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> By early February, he was in a deep shooting slump.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/story/_/id/7553888/the-hype-machine-tim-hardaway-jr-slump-north-carolina-duke-doug-mcdermott-college-basketball|title=The Hype: Duke-UNC disappointment|accessdate=2012-03-19|date=2012-02-08|author=Medcalf, Myron|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/colleges/michigan/basketball/story/_/id/7546272/tim-hardaway-jr-slumping-michigan-wolverines|title=Hardaway hits bottom at Spartans: Season low for sophomore leaves U-M 2-4 when he doesn't reach double digits|accessdate=2012-03-19|date=2012-02-06|author=Jennings, Chantel|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/article/20120208/SPORTS0201/202080311|title=Tim Hardaway Jr. fights slump at pivotal part of Michigan's season|accessdate=2012-03-19|date=2012-02-08|author=Beard, Ron|work=[[The Detroit News]]}}</ref> He posted his second double-double of the season and third of his career on March 1 against [[2011<U+2013>12 Illinois Fighting Illini men's basketball team|Illinois]] with 25 points and a career-high 11 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/boxscore?gameId=320610356|title=(16) Michigan 72 (22-8, 12-5 Big Ten), Illinois 61(17-13, 6-11 Big Ten)|accessdate=2012-03-02|date=2012-03-01|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-baskbl/recaps/030112aad.html|title=Postgame Notes: #13 Michigan 72, Illinois 61|accessdate=2013-01-11|date=2012-03-01|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=MGoBlue.com}}</ref> As a sophomore, he earned the 2011<U+2013>12 All-Big Ten 3rd team recognition by the coaches and media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/030512aad.html|title=Big Ten Announces 2012 Men's Basketball Postseason Honors: Michigan State's Green named Big Ten Player of the Year|accessdate=2012-03-06|date=2012-03-05|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|work=BigTen.org}}</ref>

